         <abstract id="aspace_cd019ce12642e8903cb485ddb619f48e">The collection documents the business and philanthropic activities of Lewis B. Cullman. Business records include business dealings with the Allied Graphic Arts Company and Cullman's leveraged buyout of the Orkin Exterminating Company in the 1960s. Also included are two bound volumes documenting the merger of Cullman's company, Cullman Ventures, Inc., with Mead Acquisition Corporation in 1999. Personal papers include biographical information, documents relating to Cullman's relationship with Yale University, records of his philanthropic contributions to New York institutions, and publicity materials for organizations which Cullman founded or contributed to. The collection also includes audiovisual recordings documenting programs funded by Cullman, interviews, and publicity materials about Cullman and his charitable contributions. There are also photographs of Cullman taken at organizations and events related to his philanthropy. </abstract>
    
